<dl id="n35209d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35209d">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35209d"> 209(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Stuyvesent</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><i>History</i>. &mdash;Under his <font color="green">[Kieft]</font> successor, Peter Stuyvesant, a board of Nine Men was chosen <font color="green">[as a popular voice in government]</font>; and this body, objecting to the custom duties which he imposed, sent three of its number with a petition to the States-General with the result that in 1643 New Amsterdam was made a city. <small> &ldquo;NEW YORK&rdquo; <a name="EBNY" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBNY"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 621</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
